          "username": "andreasgeissler"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-16 10:25:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIf I open the navigation page on the left side, the chapter \"Integration repositories\" has a \"+\" and should show the subchapters \"Integration\", \"Testsuite\", \"Demo\",...,\n- Integration repositories\n   - Integration\n   - Testsuite\n   - Demo\n\nbut intead they are shown on the same level as the parent chapter.\n+ Integration repositories\n- Integration\n- Testsuite\n- Demo",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "8b0700aff989187a08d66310260af35710e40db6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2679,
          "name": "Andreas Geissler",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "andreas@geisibee.de",
          "username": "andreasgeissler"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-16 11:47:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nMy proposal would be to rename the index.rst to e.g. \"overview.rst\" and create a \"index.rst\" with the content like:\n\n```\n.. This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.\n.. _master_index:\n\nIntegration Project Documentation\n=================================\n\n.. toctree::\n   :maxdepth: 2\n\n   overview\n   release-notes\n```\nIt would be also possible to add other rst files to the main document\n-----------------------------------\nIn the new overview.rst it would look like that:\n```\n.. This work is licensed under a\n   Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.\n.. _integration_overview:\n\nIntegration missions\n====================\n...\n```",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
